   <section xml:id="xrefstyle-support">
      <title>Customize Individual Cross References</title>
      <para>Individual cross references can be customized with the <code>xrefstyle</code> Attribute.
      You can use the <code>%c</code>, <code>%l</code> and <code>%p</code> values from Table 4.1 in
      the xslTNG Reference Guide. Beware the %p makes sense for PDF output only, since there are no
      page numbers in HTML. There is also an additional <code>%label</code> value, which stands for
        <emphasis>the full Label</emphasis>, that is the Component`s name and Number for the
      targeted Element. The use of these percent-values is explained in the following table, where
      all cross references target the next Section called <xref linkend="syntax-highlighting"
        xrefstyle="%c"/>.</para>
      <informaltable border="1">
         
         
         <thead>
            <tr>
               <th><para>Value of <code>xref/@xrefstyle</code></para></th>
               <th><para>Result</para></th>
               <th><para>Remark</para></th>
            </tr>
         </thead>
         <tbody>
            <tr>
               <td>(<code>@xrefstyle</code> is absent)</td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting"/></td>
               <td>Default</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
               <td><code>%c</code></td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting" xrefstyle="%c"/></td>
               <td><para>Content, e. g. title of target</para></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
               <td><code>%l</code></td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting" xrefstyle="%l"/></td>
               <td><para>Label, ususally the Number of target`s title</para></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
               <td><code>%label</code></td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting" xrefstyle="%label"/></td>
               <td><para>The full Label, ususally the targets component name in its
                  language, e. g. "Section" or "Abschnittt" and its
                  Number</para></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
               <td><code>%p</code></td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting" xrefstyle="%p"/></td>
               <td><para>Target`s Page Number in PDF is displayed as <code>#</code> in
                  HTML</para></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
               <td><code>see page %p</code></td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting" xrefstyle="see page %p"/></td>
               <td><para>You can mix text and percent-letters</para></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
               <td><code>%label (%c)</code></td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting" xrefstyle="%label (%c)"/></td>
               <td><para>You can use different %-letters and combine with
                  text</para></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
               <td><code>%label (%c) at page %p</code></td>
               <td><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting"
                  xrefstyle="%label (%c) at page %p"/></td>
               <td><para>Same as before, this time with Page number in
                  PDF</para></td>
            </tr>
         </tbody>
         
      </informaltable>
      <bridgehead>Legacy values</bridgehead>
      <para>In order to support migration from XSLT 1.0 Stylesheets, xslTNG supports the
         <code>template:</code> Syntax which is explained in Bob Stytons Guide, Section
         "<link xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
            xlink:href="http://www.sagehill.net/docbookxsl/CustomXrefs.html#usingtemplate"
            >Customizing with an xrefstyle attribute / Using template:</link>". This is
         explained with the following table.</para>
      <informaltable>
         <tgroup cols="3">
            <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="2*"/>
            <thead>
               <row>
                  <entry><para>Value of <code>xref/@xrefstyle</code></para></entry>
                  <entry><para>Result</para></entry>
                  <entry><para>Remark</para></entry>
               </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
               <row>
                  <entry><code>template:the chapter numbered %n</code></entry>
                  <entry><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting"
                     xrefstyle="template:the chapter numbered %n"/></entry>
                  <entry>XSLT 1.0 Legacy Syntax</entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry><code>template:the chapter called %t</code></entry>
                  <entry><xref linkend="syntax-highlighting"
                     xrefstyle="template:the chapter called %t"/></entry>
                  <entry>XSLT 1.0 Legacy Syntax</entry>
               </row>
            </tbody>
         </tgroup>
      </informaltable>
   </section>
